<!--
  Flat urlset — correct at ~13 public routes (see docs/plans/web-solana-seo-sitemap-plan.md
  §4.10: a sitemap index is unnecessary until the public page count is in the
  hundreds; lichess.org ships no sitemap at all, chess.com uses an index only
  because of per-user/per-game page volume XFChess doesn't have yet).

  lastmod values are the real last-commit date of each page's source file
  (git log -1 --format=%ad --date=short -- <file>), not invented dates —
  Google discounts sitemaps once it catches lastmod being dishonest.

  Dynamic /tournament/:id pages are intentionally NOT enumerated here; they're
  covered by the build-time prerendering step (Phase 3 of the plan above),
  which fetches live tournament IDs at build time instead of hardcoding them
  into a static file that would immediately go stale.

  priority/changefreq are omitted: Google Search Central has confirmed both
  are ignored for crawling/ranking decisions.
-->
